args: Ahhh... This tiny pool is heaven.\nSwimming in the shade is glorious.
One of the mice was...caught by a hawk?\nBut if he struggles TOO hard while it's over\nopen water, he'llâ€”
Oh, I knew that was going to happen!
(Falling into the drink that far out from\nshore... There's no way he's beating the\ncurrent all the way back to the beach.)
*sigh* Fine. I suppose I'll come to the\nrescue. I don't have a boat, so this kiddy\npool will have to do.
*huff* *huff* You okay, bud? Oh, stop\nsplashing around already. I've got you.
Phew. There, you're fine. Just don't go\ngetting scooped up by any more birds,\nall right?
There's a good lad. Now we just have to\nget back to shore. Which...
(Gah. Of course we're caught in the\ncurrent. It's hardly a surprise, but it's\nstronger than I expected.)
(Aaand it's flowing the exact opposite\ndirection from land. Just my luck.)
Ugh... And I was making such progress on\ntoday's lounging. How did it come to this?
Lunch time, everyone! Come and eat!
Hold up, Cleo. Mitsuhide's not back.\nShe's the only one missing.
Oh, dear. Where did she go?
Hm... Out of all of us, I should think her\nthe LEAST likely to get so caught up in\nsomething she'd miss a meal.
Oh, calm down. We have a simple enough\nway back to shore. Daikokuten? You're up.
It'd be my pleasure! My wings shall deliver\nus back to dry land in two shakes of a\nmouse's tail!
One, two... One...two... Oh, it's hot...\nMercy ME, it's hot...
My apologies, Mitsuhide. My robes are the\nheight of elegance, but elegance is little\nuse against such intemperate weather...
*GASP!* Ugh, I... *cough*\nI thought I was done for.
You all right? Ugh. What was Daikokuten\nthinking, wearing all that in the middle of\nsummer?
(Well, no sense worrying about that now.\nThings are starting to look a bit dire.)
Just BREATHING in this heat is exhausting.\nMy brain isn't working at all...
It feels so nice. The raindrops are\nlukewarm against my...skin...
Huh? But I was...out at sea...
Oh... You're alive. Then, were we...?
Wait. Don't answer that.\nThe fact that I'm alive says it all.
Yes, though only just. If not for the rain,\nI fear the heat might have done you in.
So the weather...saved our lives?\nAha ha...ha ha ha.
(I've been warring against the hateful\nsummer weather, and here it has the\nnerve to come along and save my life.)
(Summer is hot and obnoxious and\ncapricious to boot. I feel toyed with.)
It's all rather infuriating. Like I'm caught\nup in the whims of a fate I can't control.
Hm? I didn't catch that, Mitsuhide.
Forget it. I'm just sitting here fuming about\nthe summer weather playing tricks on me.
There's not much of the season left, but\nyou had better believe I'll be escalating\nmy war against it after this.
